    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Visual records or representations of sound created using Fourier analysis, particularly speech, with colors or densities corresponding to time, frequency, and energy comprised in the sound. Created by a sound spectrograph. Sound specrography was developed at Bell Laboratories in the 1940s.</Note_Text>
